properties.abstract: This tour is certainly an experience, featuring a tasty ascent up to the Rhznser Alp Sura, wonderful panoramic views of the mountain scenery around Flims, the Calanda and the Graubnden Rhine valley, followed by a fast-flowing descent on single trails.
properties.description:
From the railway station at Rhzns the route takes us along the Alpstrasse up to the Rhznser Alp Sura. There are several village fountains along the way, ideal for topping up those water bottles with good, fresh Rhzns water in preparation for the ascent. As the unsurfaced track continuously winds its way upwards, it's a sweat-inducing ascent that calls on reserves of endurance. Once we have passed the culms da razn (Rhzns pasture huts), we deserve a short break at the Lag Miert mountain lake. From its idyllic high-plateau setting, the small lake radiates peace and tranquillity, strengthening our resolve before we tackle the final and somewhat flatter ascent to the Rhznser Unteralp.

By the time we hear the welcome shrieks of the marmots we know we have reached the highest point on the tour, the Alp Sura (Rhznser Oberalp). We are amply rewarded for our efforts on the ascent with stunning panoramic views of the Vorab, the Tschingelhrner, the Ringelspitz and the Calanda, the Rhine valley around Chur, and the Safier and Domleschg mountains.

The downhill run begins gently enough along the Alpstrasse to the Bonaduzer Alp il Bot. Then it really begins to gather pace at the branch-off after Scardanal before turning technical on the single trail after Salums and Prau Videun. It's a real treat, with a fast-flowing run back down to Rhzns.
